Reasoning: The paper discusses computer vision techniques for lip-reading, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. It also discusses the recognition of spoken visual units, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of machine learning algorithms for lip-reading falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for further examination of the use of visemes, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses practical factors such as video resolution, pose, and lighting, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM).
